{
  "texts": [
    "The model learns summary statistics features extracted by OpenFace, including the maximum, minimum, mean, and SD values of action units, eye gaze, and head pose.",
    "However, OpenFace primarily focuses on static images, which may not adequately capture video information across frames.",
    "In this study, we employed another pre-trained facial feature extractor called Masked Autoencoder for facial video Representation LearnINg (MARLIN) from Cai et al.",
    "MARLIN is a variational auto-encoder-based facial reconstructor that extracts spatial facial features from videos.",
    "Cai et al. (2023) reported good performance of MARLIN in downstream tasks such as in-the-wild facial expression recognition."
  ]
}